
[1]stimulate

   STIMULATE, v.t. [L., to prick, to goad, to excite; a goad.] Literally,
   to prick or goad. Hence,

   1. To excite, rouse or animate to action or more vigorous exertion by
   some pungent motive or by persuasion; as, to stimulate one by the hope
   of reward, or by the prospect of glory.

   2. In medicine, to excite or increase the action of the moving fibers
   or organs of an animal body; as, to stimulate a torpid limb; or to
   stimulate the stomach and bowels.
